    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Dirty Tactics Toolbox pg. 24</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> moderate transmutation <strong>CL</strong> 7th</p><p><strong>Price</strong> +1 bonus; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>Three times per day, when the wielder of a <em>bewildering</em> weapon makes a successful attack with this weapon, in addition to dealing the weapon's normal damage, the wielder can inflict the confused condition on that enemy for 1d6 rounds. The target can attempt a DC 17 Will saving throw each round to end this effect.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>confusion</em>; <strong>Price</strong> -</p>",
